  "texts": [
    "Cost-sensitive learning Cost-sensitive learning involves considering the different costs associated with classifying data points into various categories.",
    "Instead of treating all misclassifications equally, it takes into account the consequences of different types of errors.",
    "For example, it recognizes that misclassifying a rare positive instance as negative (more prevalent) is generally more costly than the reverse scenario.",
    "The goal is to minimize both the total cost resulting from incorrect classifications and the number of expensive errors.",
    "This approach helps prioritize the accurate identification of important cases, such as rare positive instances, in situations where the class imbalance is a concern 83."
  ],
